# Environment Configuration

# SearchBard Conference Search Portal
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your API keys

# =============================================================================
# API Keys - You need at least ONE of these for the app to fetch real data
# =============================================================================

# SerpAPI - Recommended primary source for Google Events data
# Sign up: https://serpapi.com/
# Free tier: 100 searches/month
REACT_APP_SERPAPI_API_KEY=your_serpapi_key_here

# Ticketmaster Discovery API - Secondary source for ticketed conferences
# Sign up: https://developer.ticketmaster.com/
# Free tier: 5000 requests/day
REACT_APP_TICKETMASTER_API_KEY=your_ticketmaster_api_key_here

# Eventbrite API - Optional third source (not enabled by default)
# Sign up: https://www.eventbrite.com/platform/
# To enable: Uncomment the Eventbrite section in ConferenceSearchService.ts
REACT_APP_EVENTBRITE_API_KEY=your_eventbrite_key_here

# =============================================================================
# Notes
# =============================================================================
# 
# - API keys must start with REACT_APP_ to be accessible in React
# - Never commit the .env file to version control (it's in .gitignore)
# - Restart the dev server (npm start) after modifying this file
# - Without API keys, the app will fall back to mock data for demonstration
#
# API Key Setup Instructions:
# 1. Sign up for at least one API service (SerpAPI recommended)
# 2. Copy your API key from the provider's dashboard
# 3. Replace "your_*_key_here" with your actual key
# 4. Save this file
# 5. Restart your development server
#
# Troubleshooting:
# - If you see mock data only, check that keys are correctly set
# - Check browser console for API error messages
# - Verify you haven't exceeded rate limits
# - Ensure keys don't have extra spaces or quotes
